commit.message: Completed input parser (needs to merge with master)
Hard-coded the collaging of images
Last commit of the night. Started on welcome message but did not get very far.
After realizing that .jfif images did not display the same as jpg, I removed all of the jfif images from the folder I was loading from.
Added a folder with 16 images that I am loading into the program. Also added the program that we will be running for the majority of the time (Collage_It.py)
ReadImage.py is complete. It should be used as a template and can be run but willl not be a part of the final project.
Added README and ReadImage.py (3:36am)
